[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    784[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Putting It All Together
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    785[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    786[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Here's the full pipeline assembled into a single function. This is what your Glue job or orchestration Lambda would call for a full directory refresh.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    787[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    788[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    789[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def run_full_directory_load(npi_file_key: str) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    790[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    791[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Run the full provider directory graph load pipeline.
